article.description: Natalie Berglin scored 15 points and Nicole Soulis had 13 to lead Wisconsin-Green Bay (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today; No. 24 AP) to its 16th straight win, a 72-63 victory Saturday over Wisconsin-Milwaukee.
article.headline: Wisc.-Green Bay downs Wisc.-Milwaukee for 16th straight win
article.linkText: No. 25 Wisconsin-Green Bay wins 16th straight game
article.story:
MILWAUKEE -- Natalie Berglin scored 15 points and Nicole Soulis had 13 to lead Wisconsin-Green Bay (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today; No. 24 AP) to its 16th straight win, a 72-63 victory Saturday over Wisconsin-Milwaukee.

Kayla Groh and Amanda Popp added 10 apiece for the Phoenix (19-3, 10-0 Horizon League ), who have not lost since Nov. 29 against then-No. 17 DePaul.

Tracie Edwards kept the Panthers (11-12, 7-3) in the game with 31 points and 16 rebounds. The loss ended Milwaukee's 12-game home league winning streak.

Erin Templin began a 7-0 Green Bay run with a 3-pointer for a 51-49 lead with 11:15 remaining.

The Panthers pulled within 57-56 on a free throw by Turquoise McCain with 4:01 left. Green Bay took the lead for good on a basket by Groh, followed by a 3-pointer by Berglin.

Green Bay led 36-32 at the break, closing the half with a 5-0 run.
